{{page-title "Link::CTA (Call To Action)"}}

<h2 class="dummy-h2">Link::CTA (Call To Action)</h2>

<DummyLinkCtaButtonBanner />

<section>
  <h3 class="dummy-h3">
    Overview
  </h3>

  <p class="dummy-paragraph">The Link::CTA component handles the generation of an HTML
    <code class="dummy-code">
      &lt;a&gt;</code>
    anchor element with the same exact visual appearence as the "primary"
    <LinkTo @route="components.button">Button</LinkTo>
    component, that points to an external URL.
  </p>
  <p class="dummy-paragraph">
    What do we mean by the name
    <strong>Link "CTA"</strong>? It's a link that stands out from the rest of the page, and tells the user ‚Äúthis is the
    most important action on this page‚Äù. As such, it visually presents like a button.
  </p>
</section>

<section>
  <h3 class="dummy-h3">Component API</h3>
  <p class="dummy-paragraph">Here is the API for the component:</p>
  <dl class="dummy-component-props">
    <dt>size <code>enum</code></dt>
    <dd>
      <p>Acceptable values:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>small</li>
        <li class="default">medium</li>
        <li>large</li>
      </ol>
    </dd>
    <dt>text <code>string</code></dt>
    <dd>
      <p>The text to show inside the element.</p>
      <p><em>If no text value is defined an error will be thrown.</em></p>
    </dd>
    <dt>icon <code>string</code></dt>
    <dd>
      <p>Use this parameter to show an icon. Acceptable value: any Flight icon name.</p>
    </dd>
    <dt>iconPosition <code>enum</code></dt>
    <dd>
      <p>Positions the icon before or after the text. Acceptable values:</p>
      <ol>
        <li class="default">leading</li>
        <li>trailing</li>
      </ol>
    </dd>
    <dt>isFullWidth <code>boolean</code></dt>
    <dd>
      <p>This indicates that the element should take up the full width of the parent container. The default is false.</p>
    </dd>
    <dt>href</dt>
    <dd>
      <p>This is the URL that is passed down ("splatted") as arguments to the
        <code>&lt;a&gt;</code>
        element (see URL handling for details).</p>
    </dd>
    <dt>‚Äúsplattributes‚Äù</dt>
    <dd>
      <p><code class="dummy-code">...attributes</code> spreading is supported on this component.</p>
    </dd>
  </dl>
  <p class="dummy-paragraph"><strong>üö® IMPORTANT:</strong></p>
  <p class="dummy-paragraph">Despite being very similar to the
    <LinkTo @route="components.button">Button</LinkTo>
    component, there are some important differences to take into account:</p>
  <ul>
    <li class="dummy-paragraph">the
      <code class="dummy-code">color</code>
      argument is pre-selected as
      <code class="dummy-code">primary</code>
      (it needs to stand out as "call to action")</li>
    <li class="dummy-paragraph">it doesn't have a
      <code class="dummy-code">isIconOnly</code>
      option (this would go against being a "call to action")</li>
    <li class="dummy-paragraph">it doesn't have a
      <code class="dummy-code">type</code>
      option (it's not a
      <code class="dummy-code">button</code>
      element)</li>
    <li class="dummy-paragraph">it doesn't have the
      <code class="dummy-code">isDisabled</code>
      option (links can't be disabled)</li>
  </ul>
</section>

<section>
  <h3 class="dummy-h3">
    Usage
  </h3>

  <h4 class="dummy-h4">Basic use</h4>
  <p class="dummy-paragraph">The most basic invocation requires
    <code class="dummy-code">text</code>
    to be passed and an
    <code class="dummy-code">href</code>
    value (for details on how URLs are handled see below).</p>
  {{! prettier-ignore-start }}
  <CodeBlock
    @language="markup"
    @code='
      <Hds::Link::Cta @text="Sign in" href="..." />
    '
  />
  {{! prettier-ignore-end }}
  <p class="dummy-paragraph">Renders to:</p>
  <Hds::Link::Cta @text="Sign in" href="#" />
  <p class="dummy-paragraph"><em>Notice: additional HTML attributes may be added as necessary to configure the markup
      for specific use cases.</em></p>

  <h4 class="dummy-h4">Add an icon</h4>
  <p class="dummy-paragraph">To add an icon to your element, give the
    <code class="dummy-code">@icon</code>
    a
    <a href="https://flight-hashicorp.vercel.app/">Flight icon</a>
    name:
  </p>
  {{! prettier-ignore-start }}
  <CodeBlock
    @language="markup"
    @code='
      <Hds::Link::Cta @icon="entry-point" @text="Sign in" href="..." />
    '
  />
  {{! prettier-ignore-end }}
  <p class="dummy-paragraph">Renders to:</p>
  <Hds::Link::Cta @icon="entry-point" @text="Sign in" href="#" />

  <h4 class="dummy-h4">Icon position</h4>
  <p class="dummy-paragraph">By default, if you define an icon, it is placed before the text. If you would like to
    position the icon after the text, define
    <code class="dummy-code">@iconPosition</code>:
  </p>
  {{! prettier-ignore-start }}
  <CodeBlock
    @language="markup"
    @code='
      <Hds::Link::Cta @icon="entry-point" @iconPosition="trailing" @text="Sign in" href="..." />
    '
  />
  {{! prettier-ignore-end }}
  <p class="dummy-paragraph">Renders to:</p>
  <Hds::Link::Cta @icon="entry-point" @iconPosition="trailing" @text="Sign in" href="#" />

  <h4 class="dummy-h4">Size</h4>
  <p class="dummy-paragraph">
    There are three sizes available for the component:
    <code class="dummy-code">small</code>,
    <code class="dummy-code">medium</code>
    and
    <code class="dummy-code">large</code>. The default is
    <code class="dummy-code">medium</code>. To use a different size, declare a value for
    <code class="dummy-code">@size</code>:
  </p>
  {{! prettier-ignore-start }}
  <CodeBlock
    @language="markup"
    @code='
      <Hds::Link::Cta @icon="entry-point" @text="Large sign in" @size="large" href="..." />
    '
  />
  {{! prettier-ignore-end }}
  <p class="dummy-paragraph">Renders to (with icons):</p>
  <Hds::Link::Cta @icon="entry-point" @text="Small sign in" @size="small" href="#" />
  <br />
  <Hds::Link::Cta @icon="entry-point" @text="Medium sign in" @size="medium" href="#" />
  <br />
  <Hds::Link::Cta @icon="entry-point" @text="Large sign in" @size="large" href="#" />

  <h4 class="dummy-h4">Full-width</h4>
  <p class="dummy-paragraph">
    This allows indication that the component should take up the full-width of the parent container. It is set to
    <code class="dummy-code">false</code>
    by default.
  </p>
  {{! prettier-ignore-start }}
  <CodeBlock
    @language="markup"
    @code='
      <Hds::Link::Cta @icon="entry-point" @text="Sign in" @isFullWidth={{true}} href="..." />
    '
  />
  {{! prettier-ignore-end }}
  <p class="dummy-paragraph">Renders to:</p>
  <Hds::Link::Cta @icon="entry-point" @text="Sign in" @isFullWidth={{true}} href="#" />

  <h4 class="dummy-h4">URL handling</h4>
  <p class="dummy-paragraph">
    For the component to work as expected, a
    <code class="dummy-code">href</code>
    value needs to be passed as attribute. The component automatically adds
    <code class="dummy-code">target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"</code>
    to the
    <code class="dummy-code">&lt;a&gt;</code>
    element (but their values can be overwritten passing those attributes to the component).
  </p>
  {{! prettier-ignore-start }}
  <CodeBlock
    @language="markup"
    @code='
      <Hds::Button @text="Go to HashiCorp" href="https://www.hashicorp.com" />
    '
  />
  {{! prettier-ignore-end }}
  <p class="dummy-paragraph">Renders to:</p>
  <Hds::Button @text="Go to HashiCorp" href="https://www.hashicorp.com" />
</section>

